 and doing so in a backwards compatible way. Prior","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to version 1.14 of the library the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Store","isActive":true},{"text":" type has only ever been meant to be used on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"main thread, but that contract was not enforced in any major way. If a store was interacted with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on a background thread a runtime warning would be emitted, but the compiler had no knowledge of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the type’s isolation."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That now changes in 1.14 where "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Store"},{"type":"text","text":" is now officially "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@MainActor"},{"type":"text","text":"-isolated. This has been"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"done in a way that should be 100% backwards compatible, and if you have problems please open a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-composable-architecture\/discussions"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"However, if you are using ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"strict","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" concurrency settings in your app, then there is one circumstance","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in which you may have a compilation error. If you are accessing the ","type":"text"},{"code":"store","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in a view method or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"property in Xcode <16, then you may have to mark that property as ","type":"text"},{"code":"@MainActor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":[" struct FeatureView: View {","   let store: StoreOf<Feature>"," ","   var body: some View {","     \/\/ ...","   }"," ","+  @MainActor","   var title: some View {","     Text(store.name)","   }"," }"],"syntax":"diff","type":"codeListing"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.14"]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"title":"Migrating to 1.14"},"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Store","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" type is now officially ","type":"text"},{"code":"@MainActor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" isolated.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture":{"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture (TCA, for short) is a library for building applications in a consistent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and understandable way, with composition, testing, and ergonomics in mind. It can be used in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI, UIKit, and more, and on any Apple platform (iOS, macOS, tvOS, and watchOS)."}],"type":"topic","title":"ComposableArchitecture","url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/MigratingTo1.16":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":".appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"typ